parameters.sparkScript:
fileSystem = str(getExternalFileSystem('@InputConnection1').getUri()) #s3://bucket (based on input connection)
fileSystem = fileSystem.replace("s3://", "s3a://", 1) if fileSystem.startswith("s3://") else fileSystem #replace s3 with s3a which is preferred for spark

test_csv = spark.read.csv(f"{fileSystem}/qa/automation/app-data/from-file/Delimited/comma-delimeter - diff ids/EventDatasetV2025.csv", header=True)
test_csv.show(1)

#Filter results:
test_csv = test_csv.filter(test_csv['browser'] == 'chrome')


# 10 is for number of rows and False so that results aren't trimmed. 
test_csv.show(10,False)


#This creates a temp view to allow the spark dataframe to be used in spark sql
test_csv.createOrReplaceTempView('test')

# Spark sql on the csv file that we just loaded in
csv_sql = spark.sql(""" select * from test """)
csv_sql.show()


# Doing a left join on the data
joined_df = test_csv.join(csv_sql, test_csv['visitor_id'] == csv_sql['visitor_id'], 'left')


joined_df.show(1)
 
writeToEventStore(test_csv, "@OutputTable1")


test_csv = test_csv.coalesce(1)
output_path = f"{fileSystem}/qa/test_spark_csv_output"
#"s3://bucket/Pathto/my_file/output"
test_csv.write.option("header","true").csv(output_path)
test_csv.write.mode("overwrite").option("header","true").csv(output_path)
